1
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:34,640
MANTI

2
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:05,200
Hi

3
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,480
No way

4
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,800
How can you go back on your word?

5
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,480
What kind of company is this?

6
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,640
Look at other work.

7
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:27,960
Mom.

8
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:31,840
Do you think I still want to rent the house in Xu Hui?

9
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,479
I won't rent it then.

10
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,280
Don't worry.

11
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:40,120
We have plenty of good jobs, so we can find them.

12
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,080
Where should I move my luggage tomorrow?

13
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,039
Why don't we go back to Shenzhen first?

14
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,320
Take a break

15
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,360
Then come to the autumn hunting

16
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,040
Are you here to get the takeout?

17
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:08,720
Miss Tan.

18
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,080
Give me a good review if you can.

19
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,200
What's wrong?

20
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,840
Don't you want to come back to accompany me?

21
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,760
For children who grew up in Shenzhen like Shu Tong,

22
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,880
it's a good choice to go home after graduation.

23
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,200
But for their age,

24
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:32,640
getting back together with their family

25
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:35,160
I'm afraid it means other troubles.

26
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:38,440
Chen, when are you going home?

27
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,520
On the way.

28
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,280
Go to sleep. Don't wait for me.

29
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:44,360
Are you alone or with your classmates?

30
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,440
Don't take a ride.

31
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,720
I have someone with me.

32
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,400
I'm a grown man. I'm not afraid.

33
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,560
Don't worry.

34
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:53,680
I can't sleep if you don't come back.

35
00:02:55,079 --> 00:02:55,880
Almost.

36
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,920
20 minutes left.

37
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,000
It's time to turn off the lights at your house again.

38
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,720
What else?

39
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,240
I didn't go home at 2 p.m.

40
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,720
My grandparents called the police.

41
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:11,760
I found that your grandparents haven't changed.

42
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,800
It's always you.

43
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,200
If you move out one day,

44
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,240
your grandparents will bring you food every day.

45
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,000
Are you moving or moving?

46
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,880
But I haven't figured out how to tell them.

47
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:23,160
Why are you in such a hurry?

48
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,079
The school is so far from home.

49
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:28,160
I can't work two hours a day.

50
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:31,280
This is the 14th time

51
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,079
you've been pretending to be quiet.

52
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,360
Can you take a break?

53
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:36,920
OK.

54
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,560
Miao, you should move out too.

55
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,640
How about the three of us?

56
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,840
I'll take care of the house.

57
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,720
Why? Choose one from your shake building?

58
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,880
Not one building.

59
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,880
One should be fine.

60
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,079
My parents are easy to talk.

61
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,720
At most, I promised them to go on blind dates every week.

62
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:53,520
Blind date?

63
00:03:54,079 --> 00:03:55,520
Your parents are so anxious.

64
00:03:56,720 --> 00:04:00,000
Last week, they met the daughter of the owner of the Home Furnishing City.

65
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,520
I'm going to meet the niece of Dongguan Wood Factory next week.

66
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,640
One is upstream and the other is downstream.

67
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,720
Your parents are really good at business.

68
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,280
Let me see.

69
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,240
It's not sure if you can come out or not.

70
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:14,840
But it won't be a problem for you to live with your mom.

71
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,240
What's the problem?

72
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,839
That's fine.

73
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:19,040
Don't quarrel with your mom in the middle of the night.

74
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,399
Come to my house on the Chinese New Year's Eve.

75
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,120
My grandparents thought the ancestors came

76
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,400
They got up in the middle of the night to burn incense.

77
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,280
Miao,

78
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,200
You stayed at Chen's house all night.

79
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,800
Sorry to bother you.

80
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,400
I think someone covered the curtain in front of me.

81
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,880
I forgot to open it.

82
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,400
You've reached your destination.

83
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,200
Please take your belongings with you when you get off.

84
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,040
Be careful when you open the door.

85
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:57,920
You've got the wrong door.

86
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,560
This building seems to collapse.

87
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,480
I'll get going then.

88
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,280
Water.

89
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,200
Call me if anything.

90
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,760
Where did you get the money?

91
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,320
You're back.

92
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,680
What did you buy these?

93
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,160
You don't have any money in your card.

94
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,920
You're a kid. Why do you care about money?

95
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,520
What are you doing?

96
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,200
Where did you buy it? I'll return it.

97
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,080
I need to wear these.

98
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,360
You don't even go out.

99
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,880
Who are you wearing it for, Mom?

100
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,880
Why are you doing this to me?

101
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,840
You're the only one I have.

102
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:52,680
Really?

103
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,720
Do you know I graduated from college today?

104
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,360
Mom.

105
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,360
Why did you lock the door, mom?

106
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:30,240
You've grown up after graduation.

107
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,520
You want to move out?

108
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,640
No, don't think too much.

109
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,840
I just want to live closer to my workplace.

110
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:40,400
Are you going to leave me alone?

111
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,960
No.

112
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,680
I've been taking care of you.

113
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,600
I've been paying the money back for you.

114
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,360
We have to depend on each other.

115
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,120
Don't go anywhere.

116
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,800
Just stay here.

117
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,520
I'll be with you.

118
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:58,680
Mom, can you open the door first?

119
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,480
Mom.

120
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,080
Open the door, Mom.

121
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,360
Who are you?

122
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:17,320
Aunt, we are Qin Miaomiao.

123
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,440
She left her lipstick in the car.

124
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,560
Lipstick?

125
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,560
Give it to me.

126
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:28,200
She said this lipstick was important to her.

127
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:29,600
I have to give it to her myself.

128
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,920
I'm her mother.

129
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,400
What's wrong with leaving it to me?

130
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:37,799
Auntie, can I come in?

131
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,120
Auntie, I'm thirsty.

132
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,320
Can you get me some water?

133
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,360
Auntie, I need to go to the toilet.

134
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,120
The toilet is broken.

135
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,480
Auntie, is Qin Miaomiao in the room?

136
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,680
Let's go say hello to her.

137
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,640
What are you doing?

138
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,200
No one can take her away today.

139
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,560
No one can take her away today.

140
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,520
No one can take her away. Stop!

141
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,680
Fake.

142
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,400
Song Chen? Song Chen?

143
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,080
I'm in the bathroom. I'm locked.

144
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,840
Where's the key?

145
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,680
I don't know.

146
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:54,000
Why are you pulling me?

147
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,280
Step back. Stay away from the door.

148
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:04,920
What's going on?

149
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,880
My mom is crazy.

150
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,680
Miaomiao!

151
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,520
Miaomiao, don't go.

152
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,280
You can't go. Don't go.

153
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,160
Why are you locking me up?

154
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,720
Can you control my whole life if you lock me up?

155
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,240
You said you wouldn't leave me.

156
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,680
You're a liar.

157
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,360
Liar.

158
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,400
I can't breathe when I'm with you.

159
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,480
I don't want my life to be like you.

160
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:35,920
Life?

161
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,880
Because of you,

162
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:40,000
because of you.

163
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,040
Don't go.

164
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,760
Don't go.

165
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,200
You want to get rid of me and live your own life.

166
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,360
Let me tell you.

167
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,720
No way.

168
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:57,880
Mom.

169
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,400
Mom.

170
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:01,960
Leave.

171
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,760
I said go!

172
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,680
Leave!

173
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:09,520
Leave me!

174
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,000
Let's go.

175
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,800
I knew it.

176
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,120
you would leave me alone in the end.

177
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,040
Go.

178
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,080
Don't worry.

179
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:56,080
I have nowhere else to go.

180
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,080
The second thing about growing up.

181
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,920
Where do I have to run

182
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,600
to escape from the shadow of my family?

183
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,520
Well, Miao,

184
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,880
Will your mom be okay

185
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:25,000
if she's at home alone?

186
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,720
She's just drunk.

187
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:30,080
I've been through it many times since I was a kid.

188
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,360
Miao,

189
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,240
How are you doing now?

190
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:39,680
Not bad.

191
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,560
She's still borrowing money from you.

192
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,840
Why didn't you change your ID and password?

193
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,520
Does it work?

194
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,160
The bank will find me eventually.

195
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:58,080
Miao, where are you going later?

196
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:04,120
Find a cheap hotel.

197
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,520
Hotel?

198
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,520
Look at you now.

199
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,840
Can you shut your mouth?

200
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,040
Chen is right.

201
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,320
Miao, you're wearing too little.

202
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,840
It's not safe to stay in a hotel alone.

203
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,160
Besides, you have a lot of debts.

204
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,960
Save your money to pay your debt.

205
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:26,480
Then I'll ask my college friend.

206
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,520
Let's go to the hospital first.

207
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:45,240
Are you sure you won't wake them up?

208
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:55,000
We're finally back.

209
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,720
What time is it?

210
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,360
You said 20 minutes.

211
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,560
Two hours have passed.

212
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:03,640
Good evening, grandpa and grandma. Sorry.

213
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,320
Miaomiao.

214
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,480
What happened?

215
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,760
Grandma, don't worry.

216
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,720
She's staying here tonight.

217
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,040
Have you eaten?

218
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,040
There's soup in the pot. I'll heat it up for you.

219
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,680
No need, grandparents.

220
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,920
Sorry for troubling you again.

221
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,960
I didn't see you being so polite to me.

222
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,080
Chen.

223
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:24,720
It's okay.

224
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,520
Miaomiao is so sensible. Welcome, grandpa and grandma.

225
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,680
Let's go. I'll get you some clothes.

226
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,040
Okay, thank you, Grandma.

227
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,720
What's going on?

228
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:38,800
It's a long story.

229
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,080
What is this?

230
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:54,600
Miaomiao.

231
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:57,040
Wait. I'll heat up some soup for you.

232
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,440
Thank you, Grandma.

233
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,560
What?

234
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,120
Your outfit

235
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,960
is quite funny.

236
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,280
Miaomiao,

237
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,160
You can sleep in Song Chen's bed tonight.

238
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,440
Let him sleep on the floor.

239
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,800
No, Grandma.

240
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,240
I can sleep on the sofa.

241
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:28,960
I'll share a room with you.

242
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,600
I'm afraid you might have improper thoughts about me.

243
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:32,680
You are my grandma in clothes.

244
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,760
You're my brother after taking off your clothes.

245
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,520
I really have improper thoughts about you.

246
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,360
I'll sleep on the sofa.

247
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,800
The bass aren't chasing, are they?

248
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:03,760
It should be fine.

249
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,800
Wei and the others will go another way.

250
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,200
I'll meet them.

251
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:12,000
What's wrong?

252
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:17,440
Miaomiao.

253
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:20,760
What?

254
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:22,520
You didn't even say hello to your dad.

255
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:26,960
Do you have enough money these days?

256
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,880
I've been working.

257
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:34,040
It's okay. I'll order for you.

258
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:37,760
Take it and buy something delicious.

259
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:46,320
Just take it. You don't usually have such opportunities.

260
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,720
200 yuan. Don't pretend to be generous.

261
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:15,400
It's nothing.

262
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:17,319
My parents got divorced too.

263
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,920
I'm different from you.

264
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,280
My parents are not married.

265
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,560
Don't tell anyone.

266
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,080
Thank you.

267
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:26,800
What's wrong?

268
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:30,960
Did you lock the door?

269
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,320
No.

270
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,960
Aren't you going to the toilet?

271
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,600
No.

272
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,600
I'll come in and look for the charger.

273
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,840
You're awesome.

274
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,800
Ordinary people can't sleep well in a strange environment.

275
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,360
You even acted in it.

276
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,000
I was talking in my sleep. What did I say?

277
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:13,120
You'll hear me when my phone rings next time.

278
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:14,960
Are you...

279
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,560
Grandpa and Grandma are sleeping.

280
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,080
They also said

281
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,320
ask the neighbours to see if there's a cheap house to rent tomorrow.

282
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:26,840
Really?

283
